metadata.name: Patagonia Wilderness
metadata.description:
I was walking the famous W Trek through Torres del Paine in April of 2022 and I had long separated from the rest of my group as they couldn't stand my constant stopping to take pictures.

I loved the solitude and silence of walking through this vast expanse of beautiful nature all by myself. The scene pictured here particularly stands out for me as I got to witness this gorgeous sunset hit the mountains just right and creating a reflection on the lake.

Patagonia is a place I can't wait to return to over and over again to photograph her beautiful landscapes. This shot pictured here is one of my favourites from my last trip.
